<h1 id="Section-15:-Randomness">Section 15: Randomness<a class="anchor-link" href="#Section-15:-Randomness"> </a></h1>
</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Necessities">Necessities<a class="anchor-link" href="#Necessities"> </a></h2><p><code>RANDOM(a, b)</code> - which generates and returns a random integer from a to b, inclusive. Each result is equally likely to occur. 
For example, random(1,3) could return 1, 2, or 3.</p>
<p><strong>YOU CAN ALSO ADD THESE UP</strong>
random(0,2)+random(3,4) = possibilities through 0, 1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<h2 id="Practice-Problems">Practice Problems<a class="anchor-link" href="#Practice-Problems"> </a></h2><p>answer1 = random(0,2) <br>
answer2 = random(1,5)  <br>
answer3 = answer1 + answer2</p>
<p>range: [1, 2, 3, 4, 5, 6, 7]
<br></p>
<p><strong>RNGs Question</strong> <br>
Answer: C, because it does a random number (1,6), 3 times, and this amount added would be the simulation a dice roll 3 times
<br></p>
<p><strong>Random Function</strong>
Answer: C, because since the initial value of i is two, we cannot get 3 from the random function.</p>

</div>
</div>
</div>

<h1 id="Hacks">Hacks<a class="anchor-link" href="#Hacks"> </a></h1><ol>
<li>Reflection: today I learned about how libraries work and the random library in python. I learned about how the random library can be used to create new and novel code. Libraries are pre-coded, and I should use them in my code. Similarly, we can use APIs in our code to skip collecting data ourselves or storing it for it to be flexibly used. </li>
</ol>

</div>
</div>
</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<ol>
<li>Multiple Choice Questions</li>
</ol>
<table>
<thead><tr>
<th>Question</th>
<th>Answer</th>
</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
<tr>
<td>1</td>
<td>B, the random function returns a random integer between a and b, inclusive, as seen in the practice problems</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>2</td>
<td>A, when you type <code>random.randrange</code> into the code debugger or search it up, it is clear to see that random.randrange's parameters are positionally <code>start, stop, and step</code>.</td>
</tr>
<tr>
<td>3</td>
<td>A. random.item is not a method in the random library, as seen when you use <code>dir(random)</code></td>
</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

</div>
<div class="cell border-box-sizing text_cell rendered"><div class="inner_cell">
<div class="text_cell_render border-box-sizing rendered_html">
<ol>
<li>SEQ</li>
</ol>
<p><strong>A.</strong> The advantage of using libraries is using high-level, well tested code at an instant, that doesn't require people to write it themselves or to have to test it. As a result libraries expedite coding. It also allows for flexible usage of the code you have written on your own.
<br> 
<strong>B.</strong></p>

</div>
</div>
</div>

<div class="input">

<div class="inner_cell">
    <div class="input_area">
<div class=" highlight hl-ipython3"><pre><span></span><span class="kn">import</span> <span class="nn">random</span> 
<span class="c1"># Import the random library</span>

<span class="n">names_string</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">input</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">&quot;Give me everybody&#39;s names, seperated by a comma.&quot;</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="c1"># gets the names of &quot;everybody&quot; and then splits them into a list using the .split() method</span>
<span class="n">names</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">names_string</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">split</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">&quot;,&quot;</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="n">num_items</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">names</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1"># Finds the number of items through the length of the names list</span>

<span class="n">random_choice</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">randint</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">num_items</span> <span class="o">-</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span> 
<span class="c1"># gets a random integer using the randint() function, choosing 0 (the first element) and </span>
<span class="c1"># Numitems-1 (the last index, because of 0 base indexing everything moves back one hence the -1)</span>

<span class="n">person_who_will_pay</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">names</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">random_choice</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="c1"># assigns whoever to pay with the random choice</span>

<span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="sa">f</span><span class="s2">&quot;</span><span class="si">{</span><span class="n">person_who_will_pay</span><span class="si">}</span><span class="s2"> is going to buy the meal today!&quot;</span><span class="p">)</span>
<span class="c1"># Displays the person_who_will_pay variable, an element in the names list.</span>
</pre></div>

    </div>
</div>
</div>

<span class="k">if</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">i1</span><span class="o">+</span><span class="n">i2</span> <span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="n">i3</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">i4</span><span class="p">):</span>

    <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;draw&#39;</span><span class="p">)</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">returnGoalAndRobot</span><span class="p">():</span> <span class="c1"># returns the robot, oriented at a random position</span>
    <span class="n">lst</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">90</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">180</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">270</span><span class="p">]</span>
    <span class="n">im</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">Image</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">open</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">&quot;../images/sprite.png&quot;</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1"># stored in house</span>
    <span class="n">im2</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">Image</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">new</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;RGB&#39;</span><span class="p">,(</span><span class="mi">100</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">100</span><span class="p">),(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">255</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">))</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">all_same</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">TwoDMatrix</span><span class="p">):</span> <span class="c1"># contingency, checks to make sure all have the same length</span>
    <span class="k">try</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="n">constant</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">TwoDMatrix</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">])</span>
        <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">array</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">TwoDMatrix</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="k">if</span> <span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">array</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="o">!=</span> <span class="n">constant</span><span class="p">:</span>
                <span class="k">return</span> <span class="kc">False</span>
    <span class="k">except</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="kc">False</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="kc">True</span> <span class="c1"># returns true if everything is the same, returns false otherwise</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">generate_from_array</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">TwoDMatrix</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">pixel</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="mi">100</span><span class="p">):</span> <span class="c1"># generates the board using info stored in TwoDMatrix</span>
    <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">all_same</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">TwoDMatrix</span><span class="p">):</span> <span class="c1"># checks if everything is the same</span>
        <span class="n">height</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">TwoDMatrix</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1"># sets height and length equal to various heights/widths</span>
        <span class="n">length</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="nb">len</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">TwoDMatrix</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">])</span>
        <span class="n">paste_img</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">Image</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">new</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;RGB&#39;</span><span class="p">,(</span><span class="n">pixel</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">pixel</span><span class="p">),(</span><span class="mi">255</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">255</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">255</span><span class="p">))</span> <span class="c1"># inits images</span>
        <span class="n">player_im</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">returnGoalAndRobot</span><span class="p">()[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span> 
        <span class="n">goal_im</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">returnGoalAndRobot</span><span class="p">()[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]</span>

    <span class="k">else</span><span class="p">:</span>
        <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">Image</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">open</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">&quot;../images/err.png&quot;</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1"># error image</span>
    <span class="n">contact_sheet</span><span class="o">=</span><span class="n">PIL</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">Image</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">new</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s1">&#39;RGB&#39;</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">pixel</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n">length</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="n">pixel</span><span class="o">*</span><span class="n">height</span><span class="p">))</span> <span class="c1"># creates a sheet using the length and height</span>
    <span class="n">box_Coord</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="c1"># sets coordinates to draw images</span>
    <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">array</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">TwoDMatrix</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="c1"># loops over the 2d matrix array (parameter)</span>
        <span class="k">for</span> <span class="nb">bin</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="n">array</span><span class="p">:</span>
            <span class="k">if</span> <span class="nb">bin</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="c1"># if the item is 1, that is a wall</span>
                <span class="n">contact_sheet</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">paste</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">paste_img</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">box_Coord</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">],</span>  <span class="n">box_Coord</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">])</span> <span class="p">)</span>
            <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="nb">bin</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="mi">2</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="c1"># if the item is two (which there is only 1) that is the player</span>
                <span class="n">contact_sheet</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">paste</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">player_im</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">box_Coord</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">box_Coord</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]))</span>
            <span class="k">elif</span> <span class="nb">bin</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="mi">3</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="c1"># if the item is three (which there is only 1) that is the goal</span>
                <span class="n">contact_sheet</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">paste</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">goal_im</span><span class="p">,</span> <span class="p">(</span><span class="n">box_Coord</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">],</span> <span class="n">box_Coord</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]))</span>
            <span class="k">else</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="c1"># otherwise 0, pass</span>
                <span class="k">pass</span>
            <span class="k">if</span> <span class="n">box_Coord</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">+</span> <span class="n">pixel</span> <span class="o">&gt;</span> <span class="n">contact_sheet</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">width</span><span class="o">-</span><span class="n">pixel</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="c1"># if we go over bounds the image</span>
                <span class="n">box_Coord</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">0</span>
                <span class="n">box_Coord</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="n">pixel</span> <span class="c1"># loop back</span>
            <span class="k">else</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="c1"># otherwise advance</span>
                <span class="n">box_Coord</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]</span> <span class="o">+=</span> <span class="n">pixel</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">contact_sheet</span> <span class="c1"># return when finished</span>

<span class="k">def</span> <span class="nf">setup</span><span class="p">():</span> <span class="c1"># consolidating setup for easy usage</span>
    <span class="n">grid</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[[</span><span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">randint</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">)],</span> 
    <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">randint</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">)],</span> <span class="c1"># create a random grid using list comprehensions</span>
    <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">randint</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">)],</span>
    <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">randint</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">)],</span>
    <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">randint</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">)]]</span>
    <span class="n">player_start</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">randint</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">randint</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">)]</span> <span class="c1"># find player start and stop</span>
    <span class="n">goal_start</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">randint</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">randint</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">)]</span>
    <span class="k">while</span> <span class="n">goal_start</span> <span class="o">==</span> <span class="n">player_start</span><span class="p">:</span> <span class="c1"># contingency, make sure they aren&#39;t equal</span>
        <span class="n">goal_start</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="p">[</span><span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">randint</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">),</span> <span class="n">random</span><span class="o">.</span><span class="n">randint</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">,</span><span class="mi">4</span><span class="p">)]</span>
    <span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">player_start</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]][</span><span class="n">player_start</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">2</span>
    <span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="n">goal_start</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">0</span><span class="p">]][</span><span class="n">goal_start</span><span class="p">[</span><span class="mi">1</span><span class="p">]]</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="mi">3</span>
    <span class="k">return</span> <span class="n">generate_from_array</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">grid</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1"># return the generated array using grid</span>

<span class="k">for</span> <span class="n">i</span> <span class="ow">in</span> <span class="nb">range</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="mi">5</span><span class="p">):</span> <span class="c1"># do this 5 times, to display randomness</span>
    <span class="n">d</span> <span class="o">=</span> <span class="n">setup</span><span class="p">()</span>
    <span class="nb">print</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="s2">&quot;legend: Walls = black, spaces = white, goal = green, red triangle = player&quot;</span><span class="p">)</span>
    <span class="n">display</span><span class="p">(</span><span class="n">d</span><span class="p">)</span> <span class="c1"># display the image</span>
